4.3. WorkÔ¨Çows and Quality Ratings
A concrete deployment or link is thus described by an attribute vector Ai ‚àà Di . In the optimization context,
this attribute vector is mapped to a quality vector Qi = normi (Ai ) by applying the respective normalization map to
each single attribute. Each quality vector Qi has an associated vector wi that, for each attribute, deÔ¨Ånes its weight.
An abstract workÔ¨Çow is the representation of a sequence of invoked services (can be in parallel) to meet a certain
requirement (satisfy a given request).

